The paper deals with the development of a structure learning algorithm for a class of multivariate stable densities, which can be represented as Bayesian networks. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of the algorithm for gene expression data analysis, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) and statistical theory (cs.ST) in establishing the theoretical properties of the algorithm.
